FOLLOWING the injury of Percy Tau, Akram Tawfik, Salah Mohsen and Badr Benoun, Al Ahly have suffered another major blow. The club head coach Pitso Mosimane has joined the long list of personnel that will miss the first match o0f the tournament on Saturday after testing positive for Covid-19. The Egyptian giants are currently at the United Arab Emirates preparing for their Fifa Club World Cup. However, On Wednesday, they were rocked by the news that their coach had tested positive for Covid-19. Ahmed Abu Abla, Al Ahly's doctor, stated that "Pitso Mosimane, Al Ahly head coach, tested positive for COVID-19." Abu Abla said that Mosimane underwent another COVID-19 test today. The team's doctor added that our coach's condition is stable, and he is currently self-isolated. Ahly will kick off the tournament with a clash against CONCACAF representatives Monterrey on Saturday. For the first match, Al Ahly will also be without Mohamed El-Shennawy, Ayman Ashraf, Mohamed Abdelmoneim, Hamdi Fathi, Amr El-Sulya, and Mohamed Sherif, who are currently with the Egypt national team at the Africa Cup of Nations in Morocco. Ahly are heading to the tournament hoping to improve from last season feat where they finished third to claim a bronze medal.